<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17680706-3">
               <interp inst="t17680706-3" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680706-3" type="year" value="1768"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680706-3" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17680706"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17680706-3" type="date" value="17680706"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17680706-3-off14-c42" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-3-defend48 t17680706-3-off14 t17680706-3-verdict17"></join>
         
               <p>409. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17680706-3-defend48" type="defendantName">
                     Robert 
                     Iveson 
                  <interp inst="t17680706-3-defend48" type="surname" value="Iveson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-defend48" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-defend48" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17680706-3-off14" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-off14" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-off14" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one hundred pounds weight of sugar, value 26 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17680706-3-victim50" type="victimName">
                     Samuel 
                     Vaughan 
                  <interp inst="t17680706-3-victim50" type="surname" value="Vaughan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-victim50" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-victim50" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-3-off14 t17680706-3-victim50"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17680706-3-cd15" type="crimeDate">June 30</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-3-off14 t17680706-3-cd15"></join>. +</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680706-3-person51">
                  Thomas 
                  Crofts 
               <interp inst="t17680706-3-person51" type="surname" value="Crofts"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person51" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person51" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 30th of June I heard a hammering in a lighter that lay a long side a ship, 
               <persName id="t17680706-3-person52">
                  Samuel 
                  Vaughan 
               <interp inst="t17680706-3-person52" type="surname" value="Vaughan"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person52" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person52" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             is owner, to which I belong; I went into the lighter loaded with sugar in Shadwell-dock, there I saw the prisoner hammering the head of a cask; he throwed down the hammer; I found two handkerchiefs of sugar, containing one hundred weight, about three or four feet from him; I secured him, he begged to be let go; I found the head had been taken off; the prisoner belongs to the lighter; there was another man in the lighter at the other end of her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>The sugar was lying there when I went down there, I was not hammering the cask.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680706-3-person53">
                  John 
                  Shaw 
               <interp inst="t17680706-3-person53" type="surname" value="Shaw"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person53" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person53" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner has worked for me between three and four years as a <rs id="t17680706-3-deflabel16" type="occupation">lighterman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17680706-3-defend48 t17680706-3-deflabel16"></join>; I can say nothing ill of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680706-3-person54">
                  Richard 
                  Webb 
               <interp inst="t17680706-3-person54" type="surname" value="Webb"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person54" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person54" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known the prisoner upwards of fourteen years; he has worked for me, and always behaved like an honest man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17680706-3-person55">
                  John 
                  Jollet 
               <interp inst="t17680706-3-person55" type="surname" value="Jollet"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person55" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-person55" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He has worked for me; I never found him otherwise but honest and industrious.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17680706-3-verdict17" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17680706-3-verdict17" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
